The given equation in the problem is:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{P}_0&=\dfrac{\text{E}_1(1-\text{b})}{\text{R}_S-\text{ROE}\times\text{b}}
\end{aligned}$$

Where,

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{P}_0&=\text{Current price of share}\\
\text{E}_1&=\text{Earnings for the next period}\\
\text{b}&=\text{Retention ratio}\\
\text{R}_S&=\text{Cost of equity capital}\\
\text{ROE}&=\text{Return on equity}
\end{aligned}$$
